As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 1,280 people, 540 households, and 372 families residing in the borough. The population density was {{convert|2,293.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 558 housing units at an average density of {{convert|999.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the borough was 98.67% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.16% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.08% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.47% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.16% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], and 0.47% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.08% of the population.

There were 540 households, out of which 28.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 58.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 7.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.1% were non-families. 27.2% of all households were made up of individuals, and 14.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.36 and the average family size was 2.87.

In the borough the population was spread out, with 22.7% under the age of 18, 6.3% from 18 to 24, 27.2% from 25 to 44, 22.8% from 45 to 64, and 20.9% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 41 years. For every 100 females, there were 93.6 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 85.9 males.

The median income for a household in the borough was $35,132, and the median income for a family was $41,450. Males had a median income of $31,172 versus $22,500 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the borough was $17,348. About 4.0% of families and 5.3% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 3.5% of those under age 18 and 6.6% of those age 65 or over.

